---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | JILBIT"
  description="How JILBIT collects, uses, and protects information when you use jilbit.com."
>
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-[#000000] px-6 py-14 text-left md:py-20">
    <div
      class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 bg-[radial-gradient(circle_at_center,rgba(201,146,42,0.14),transparent_55%)]"
    />
    <div class="content-shell relative">
      <p class="text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-[#5cd667]">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="mt-4 max-w-4xl text-4xl leading-tight text-[#faf7f2] md:text-5xl">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-[#faf7f2]/60">Last updated: April 18, 2026</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-[#f0ebe0] px-6 py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="content-shell">
      <article
        class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-8 rounded-lg border border-[rgba(92,61,46,0.15)] bg-white p-8 shadow-sm md:p-12 [&_h2]:mt-10 [&_h2]:text-xl [&_h2]:font-semibold [&_h2]:text-[#2e1a0e] [&_h2]:first:mt-0 [&_p]:leading-relaxed [&_ul]:list-disc [&_ul]:pl-6 [&_li]:text-[#7a6658]"
      >
        <p class="text-lg text-[#7a6658]">
          JILBIT (“we,” “us,” or “our”) respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy describes how we may collect, use, and share
          information when you visit <strong class="text-[#2e1a0e]">jilbit.com</strong> (the “Site”) or interact with our ministry
          online.
        </p>

        <h2>1. Information we may collect</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-[#7a6658]">
          <li>
            <strong class="text-[#2e1a0e]">Information you provide:</strong> such as name, email address, mailing address, or message
            content when you contact us, subscribe to updates, register for events, or make a donation.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-[#2e1a0e]">Transaction information:</strong> payment-related details processed by our payment
            providers (we typically do not store full card numbers on our servers).
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-[#2e1a0e]">Technical data:</strong> such as browser type, device type, general location (e.g.,
            region), and pages visited, collected through cookies or similar technologies where used.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>2. How we use information</h2>
        <p class="text-[#7a6658]">We may use information to:</p>
        <ul class="text-[#7a6658]">
          <li>Operate, maintain, and improve the Site and ministry communications</li>
          <li>Respond to inquiries and provide requested resources</li>
          <li>Process donations, orders, or event registrations</li>
          <li>Comply with legal obligations and protect our rights and users</li>
          <li>Analyze aggregate usage to improve content and user experience</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. Cookies and similar technologies</h2>
        <p class="text-[#7a6658]">
          We may use cookies or similar tools to remember preferences or measure traffic. You can control cookies through your
          browser settings. If we use analytics or marketing tools, we will aim to configure them consistent with this Policy and
          applicable law.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Sharing of information</h2>
        <p class="text-[#7a6658]">
          We do not sell your personal information. We may share information with service providers who assist us (e.g., hosting,
          email, payment processing) subject to appropriate safeguards, or when required by law or to protect safety and rights.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Data retention</h2>
        <p class="text-[#7a6658]">
          We retain information only as long as needed for the purposes described here, unless a longer period is required by law
          or for legitimate ministry records (e.g., donation acknowledgments).
        </p>

        <h2>6. Children’s privacy</h2>
        <p class="text-[#7a6658]">
          The Site is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.
          If you believe we have, please contact us and we will take appropriate steps.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Your choices and rights</h2>
        <p class="text-[#7a6658]">
          Depending on where you live, you may have rights to access, correct, or delete certain personal information, or to
          object to certain processing. To make a request, contact us at the email below. We may need to verify your identity.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Security</h2>
        <p class="text-[#7a6658]">
          We use reasonable measures to protect information, but no method of transmission over the Internet is 100% secure.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Changes to this Policy</h2>
        <p class="text-[#7a6658]">
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The “Last updated” date will reflect changes. We encourage you to
          review this page periodically.
        </p>

        <h2>10. Contact</h2>
        <p class="text-[#7a6658]">
          For privacy questions, contact us at <a href="mailto:info@jilbit.com" class="text-[#2d4a3e] underline underline-offset-2"
            >info@jilbit.com</a
          >.
        </p>

        <p class="border-t border-[rgba(92,61,46,0.15)] pt-8 text-sm text-[#7a6658]/90">
          <strong class="text-[#2e1a0e]">Note:</strong> This is a general template. JILBIT should have qualified counsel review this
          Privacy Policy for compliance with applicable laws (e.g., state privacy laws, GDPR if relevant).
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
